  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together coriander powder, cumin powder, paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the sliced onion, minced garlic, and grated ginger to the bowl and toss to coat.",
    "Add the minari shoots to the bowl and toss to combine.",
    "Heat the olive oil in a large oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the cured beef strips and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side, until browned.",
    "Transfer the skillet to the preheated oven and roast for 12-15 minutes.",
    "Remove the skillet from the oven and add the lemon juice to the bowl with the minari and onion mixture.",
    "Toss the mixture to combine and add it to the skillet with the cured beef.",
    "Return the skillet to the oven and roast for an additional 5-7 minutes, until the minari is tender.",
    "Remove the skillet from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes before serving."
  ],
